FBIS3-12351 "drnes039_n_94002" FBIS-NES-94-039 Document Type:Daily Report 28 Feb 1994 LEBANON 8 dead, 25 Injured NC2702085894 Beirut Voice of Lebanon in Arabic 0837 GMT 27 Feb 94 NC2702085894 Beirut Voice of Lebanon Language: Arabic Article Type:BFN [Text] Just in from the editor's desk: According to a report by the Security Forces, there are so far eight dead and 25 injured in the church explosion. The security forces reported that another explosive charge that was planted inside the church did not go off. A military expert was summoned to defuse it. This is the latest report from the security forces. Naturally, after the explosion there was commotion and the situation is worrisome there. That is why we have been unable to obtain accurate information, because the security forces are touring the hospitals to report on the death toll and names of the casualties. To repeat: There are eight dead and 25 injured as of now and the security forces are defusing another explosive charge that did not go off. The other charge was certainly planted to cause a large number of casualties. The explosive charges were placed in the church to explode. This was reported by the security forces. The confirmed report is that there are eight dead and 25 injured so far.
